OL,3,CWar propels BP back into 'cash money'
OL,4,Cterritory
OL,6,FA former chief executive once
OL,7,Fdescribed BP as a "cash machine" when
OL,8,Fthe price of Brent Crude was around
OL,9,F$85 a barrel.
OL,11,FA lot has changed since Bernard Looney
OL,12,Fmade that statement five years ago -
OL,13,Fhe's no longer there for a start - but
OL,14,Fas a ready reckoner it still holds.
OL,15,FAnd today Brent is back above $110.
OL,17,FWar in the Middle East has
OL,18,Fsupercharged BP's profits. A headline
OL,19,Fprofit of #2.4 billion for the period
OL,20,FJanuary to March isn't bad going.
OL,26,@oD@SOUoD@`O]
